('generate_with_fc', '{"args":[],"func":"generate_with_fc","kwargs":{"functions":[],"messages":[{"content":"You are designing a public location map for a role-play simulation world.\\n\\n## World Setting\\n## Bremer Apartment\\nBremer Apartment stands on a quiet street in Greenwich Village, Manhattan. It is a six-story brick building built in the 1920s. All kinds of people live in the building: actors, lawyers, students, musicians, waiters, programmers, and immigrant families. They come from different states and different countries, yet somehow they end up sharing the same staircase, the same hallway, and the same thin apartment walls. In New York, buildings like this often witness the same quiet transformation: strangers slowly become friends, friends become lovers, and lovers eventually become neighbors who can no longer avoid each other.\\n\\n## Familiar Places in the Building\\n1. The Rooftop (Sixth Floor)\\nAn old water tower stands on the roof. On summer nights, tenants bring beer and folding chairs upstairs and sit together under the warm city sky.\\n2. The Corner Coffee Shop\\nMost residents visit it almost every day. It feels like the apartment\'s second living room.\\n\\n## What the Building Means\\n\\nTo New York City, this building is just one apartment among thousands.\\nBut to the people who live here, it represents:\\nthe confusion of youth\\nthe trial and error of love\\nthe companionship of friends\\nthose first uncertain years when life is just beginning\\nMany years later, the residents may move away.\\n\\nWorld name: apartment\\nLanguage: English\\nNumber of locations: 30\\n\\n# Characters in this world\\n## Aaron Whitfield\\nAaron is a freelance journalist and aspiring novelist who moved to Bremer Apartment in 2019. He\'s working on a debut novel about immigrant families in New York while scraping together income from maga ... (156 more chars omitted)\\n\\n## Adrian Morales\\nAdrian is a playwright and bartender at Chez Lulu who moved into Bremer Apartment in late 2019. He\'s talented, self-critical, and struggling to finish his first full-length play. He had developed feel ... (110 more chars omitted)\\n\\n## Adrian Vale\\nAdrian is the estranged youngest son of Marcus Vale, a legendary investment banking executive on Wall Street. After a bitter falling-out with his father during his junior year at Columbia, Adrian drop ... (392 more chars omitted)\\n\\nRequirements:\\n1. Generate exactly 30 public locations that fit this world\'s setting\\n2. Each location needs:\\n - display_name: the location name\\n - size: \\"small\\", \\"medium\\", or \\"large\\"\\n - description: 4-6 sentences describing the place (include spatial layout, atmosphere)\\n - objects: 5-6 items found there\\n3. Mix of sizes: roughly 50% small, 35% medium, 15% large\\n4. Do NOT include private homes\\n5. Avoid real-world brand names or proper nouns\\n6. IMPORTANT: All strings must be valid JSON. Escape any quotes inside strings with backslash (e.g., \\"sign says \\\\\\"Hello\\\\\\"\\" not \\"sign says \\"Hello\\"\\")\\n\\nOutput ONLY valid JSON in this format (use actual descriptive location names, NOT placeholder names like \\"Location1\\"):\\n{\\"public\\": {\\"Cafeteria\\": {\\"display_name\\": \\"Cafeteria\\", \\"size\\": \\"large\\", \\"description\\": \\"...\\", \\"objects\\": [\\"item1\\", \\"item2\\"]}, \\"Library\\": {\\"display_name\\": \\"Library\\", \\"size\\": \\"large\\", \\"description\\": \\"...\\", \\"objects\\": [...]}, ...}}\\n","role":"user"}],"model":"my-vllm-model","tool_choice":"none"}}')
