('generate_with_fc', '{"args":[],"func":"generate_with_fc","kwargs":{"functions":[],"messages":[{"content":"Based on the persona profile, generate a brief description of the character\'s home (bedroom/room) and representative objects.\\n\\nProfile:\\nName: Adrian Morales\\nAppearance: Standing 6\'0\\" and roughly 175 lbs with a rangy, angular build, Adrian registers as attractive (~10%) in a sharp, slightly theatrical way. He has deep-set dark eyes beneath heavy brows, a strong Roman ... (774 more chars omitted)\\nDescription: Adrian is a playwright and bartender at Chez Lulu who moved into Bremer Apartment in late 2019. He\'s talented, self-critical, and struggling to finish his first full-length play. He had developed feelings for his coworker Katie, who moved to Los Angeles in January 2020, and is still adjusting to her absence.\\n\\nDetails: Adrian moved into a cramped fourth-floor studio at Bremer Apartment in November 2019 after his previous roommate situation in Bushwick imploded. He\'d heard about the opening from Katie, who he\'d been working with at Chez Lulu since mid-2019. They bonded quickly over shared creative frustrations — her auditions going nowhere, his play stuck in rewrites. He\'s drawn to her intensity, the same quality Marcus called \\"too much,\\" which Adrian finds brave and honest. But he watched her go through the Marcus breakup in December 2019 and decided the timing was wrong to say anything. He tells himself he\'s being respectful; in truth, he\'s also afraid. He met Leo through Katie and likes him genuinely — they\'ve had good rooftop conversations about music and storytelling — but he senses Leo\'s unspoken feelings for Katie, which creates a quiet, unacknowledged rivalry between them. Adrian\'s play, titled \\"Elevation,\\" is loosely about a Bronx family navigating gentrification; he\'s terrified it\'s either too personal or not personal enough. His mother calls every Sunday and asks when he\'s going to get a real job. He sends money home monthly, which keeps him perpetually broke. He writes at the corner coffee shop most mornings, occupying the same window table.\\n\\nOutput JSON: {\\"description\\": <2-4 sentences>, \\"objects\\": [4-6 item names]}\\nOutput in en.","role":"user"}],"model":"my-vllm-model","tool_choice":"none"}}')
