('generate_with_fc', '{"args":[],"func":"generate_with_fc","kwargs":{"functions":[],"messages":[{"content":"Based on the persona profile, generate a brief description of the character\'s home (bedroom/room) and representative objects.\\n\\nProfile:\\nName: Adrian Vale\\nAppearance: Standing 6\'1\\" and about 170 lbs with a long, angular frame that suggests old money even in thrift-store clothing, Adrian has an attractive (~10%) face defined by sharp cheekbones, a strong aquiline no ... (792 more chars omitted)\\nDescription: Adrian is the estranged youngest son of Marcus Vale, a legendary investment banking executive on Wall Street. After a bitter falling-out with his father during his junior year at Columbia, Adrian dropped out, severed financial ties, and moved into a small studio at Bremer Apartment in 2018. He now works part-time at the corner coffee shop alongside Juniper, earning just enough to cover rent and food. He spends his remaining hours wandering the city, reading philosophy, and sitting on the rooftop trying to understand what he wants from a life he was never allowed to choose for himself.\\n\\nDetails: Adrian\'s break with his father came in early 2016 after Marcus demanded he transfer to Wharton and join Vale Capital. Adrian refused. Marcus froze his trust fund and told him he was throwing away everything the family had built. Adrian\'s older brother, Nathan, sided with their father. His mother sends him quiet, desperate texts he rarely answers. He moved into Bremer Apartment in the summer of 2018 after couch-surfing and subletting for two years. He found the coffee shop job through a flyer in the building\'s lobby. Juniper trained him and they became co-workers and tentative friends. On the rooftop, he met Daniel one autumn evening in 2019 — they argued about whether privilege is a debt or a fact, and kept talking for three hours. He also met Leo up there, drawn by the guitar playing; they share quiet companionship and occasional beers. He has noticed Vera coming and going at odd hours but has never pried. He lives frugally — his studio has a mattress on the floor, stacked books, and nothing on the walls. He has not spoken to his father in four years. He sometimes walks past Vale Capital\'s Midtown office and stands across the street, watching the revolving doors, feeling nothing he can name.\\n\\nOutput JSON: {\\"description\\": <2-4 sentences>, \\"objects\\": [4-6 item names]}\\nOutput in en.","role":"user"}],"model":"my-vllm-model","tool_choice":"none"}}')
